ce:section.ce:para:
The developed N,S-CDs nano sensor was successfully applied for determination of NFZ in SGJ over the concentration range of 3.0–20.0 μM as shown in Fig. 7
                           . SGJ containing NFZ was omitted for blank experiment. LOD and LOQ were 0.34 and 1.04 μM, respectively (Table 7
                           ) which indicate the proposed method sensitivity for NFZ analysis in SGJ. Statistical examination of the obtained data demonstrated high % recovery (98.03–101.52 %) and low % RSD (less than 2 %) which indicate high level of accuracy and precision, respectively (Table 8
                           ). No interference was encountered from components of SGJ which validate the method for real applications. The promising results for determination of NFZ in SGJ pave the way for the synthesized nano sensor for application in drug release studies.
